Scripts do not have parameters. The next section describe how to modify the parameters
of each module.

\section config_sec Configuration Files

config files for all servers are located in the repository at $ICUB_DIR/src/primateVision/config

you can specify alternate config files at server start-up by using "-c FILE".


\section example_sec How to run the application

\subsection starting Starting the application

- Start left and right dragonfly servers and icubInterface2. 

- Start the recserver. 

- You can start direct recserver clients (egosphere2, recclient).

- Start any of: tsbserver, ycsserver, colcsserver, ocsserver, flowserver, (these use left camera config file by default, but you can specify to use the right manually by typing "ycsserver -c $ICUB_DIR/src/primateVision/config/ycsL.cfg", for example), depthflowserver(stereo), zdfserver (stereo).

- Start dependent clients (eg, "ycsclient l", "svogrid"), or dependent servers (eg, salserver, iorserver, where for example sal server depends on above input servers as configured in salL.cfg).

-Start any attention clients.



